[SN]TITLE[SN]
CCTV image issued over bus attack in Musselburgh

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A CCTV image has been released of a man police wish to speak to in connection with an assault and robbery on a night bus in East Lothian.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The N44 bus was travelling in the  Newbigging area of Musselburgh at 03:40 on Sunday 5 July when the attack happened.
The man is white, 18-21 years old, 5ft 9in tall, of slim build, with dark hair and a Scottish accent.
He was wearing a dark jumper, jeans and black shoes at the time.
Det Con Stephen McCormick said: "This robbery has been a terrifying experience for the victim and other passengers on the bus and our officers have been making extensive enquiries to find the person responsible.
"We would urge anyone who may recognise the man pictured or is able to provide any information that might help our investigations to get in touch immediately."
